---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
const title = "Terms of Service - Airgap Gate";
const effectiveDate = "February 22, 2026";
---
<BaseLayout title={title}>
    <Header />

    <!-- Content -->
    <main class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-16">
        <h1 class="text-4xl font-extrabold text-slate-900 mb-2" style="font-family: 'Plus Jakarta Sans', sans-serif;">Terms of Service</h1>
        <p class="text-slate-500 mb-12">Effective Date: {effectiveDate}</p>

        <div class="prose prose-slate max-w-none space-y-8">
            <section>
                <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-3">1. Acceptance of Terms</h2>
                <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">
                    By accessing or using Airgap Gate ("Service"), you agree to be bound by these Terms of Service ("Terms").
                    If you do not agree to these Terms, you may not access or use the Service. These Terms apply to all users,
                    including healthcare providers, administrators, and any other individuals who access the Service.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-3">2. Description of Service</h2>
                <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">
                    Airgap Gate provides AI-powered prior authorization intelligence tools designed to assist healthcare
                    providers in managing prior authorization workflows. The Service includes predictive analytics,
                    documentation guidance, and formulary alternative suggestions. The Service is intended as a
                    decision-support tool and does not replace professional medical or legal judgment.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-3">3. Eligibility</h2>
                <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">
                    You must be at least 18 years of age and authorized to act on behalf of a healthcare organization
                    to use this Service. By using the Service, you represent that you meet these requirements.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-3">4. Account Registration</h2>
                <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">
                    To access certain features, you may be required to create an account. You agree to provide accurate
                    and complete information, maintain the security of your credentials, and promptly notify us of any
                    unauthorized use of your account. You are responsible for all activities that occur under your account.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-3">5. Acceptable Use</h2>
                <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mb-3">You agree not to:</p>
                <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-slate-600 space-y-2">
                    <li>Use the Service for any unlawful purpose or in violation of applicable healthcare regulations.</li>
                    <li>Attempt to gain unauthorized access to any part of the Service or its related systems.</li>
                    <li>Reverse engineer, decompile, or disassemble any aspect of the Service.</li>
                    <li>Use the Service to store or transmit malicious code or content.</li>
                    <li>Resell, sublicense, or redistribute access to the Service without written permission.</li>
                </ul>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-3">6. Healthcare Disclaimer</h2>
                <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">
                    Airgap Gate is a decision-support tool. It does not provide medical advice, diagnosis, or treatment
                    recommendations. All clinical decisions remain the responsibility of the treating healthcare provider.
                    Predictions, approval probabilities, and documentation suggestions are generated by machine learning
                    models and should be used as informational guidance only. Airgap Gate does not guarantee the outcome
                    of any prior authorization submission.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-3">7. Data and Privacy</h2>
                <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">
                    Your use of the Service is also governed by our <a href="/privacy" class="text-sky-600 hover:text-sky-700 underline">Privacy Policy</a>.
                    By using the Service, you consent to the collection and use of data as described therein.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-3">8. Intellectual Property</h2>
                <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">
                    All content, features, and functionality of the Service — including but not limited to algorithms,
                    models, software, text, graphics, and trademarks — are owned by Airgap Gate and are protected by
                    intellectual property laws. You may not copy, modify, or create derivative works based on the Service
                    without express written consent.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-3">9. Limitation of Liability</h2>
                <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">
                    To the maximum extent permitted by applicable law, Airgap Gate shall not be liable for any indirect,
                    incidental, special, consequential, or punitive damages arising from your use of the Service, including
                    but not limited to denial of prior authorization requests, delays in patient care, or loss of revenue.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-3">10. Modifications to Terms</h2>
                <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">
                    We reserve the right to modify these Terms at any time. Changes will be posted on this page with an
                    updated effective date. Your continued use of the Service after changes are posted constitutes
                    acceptance of the revised Terms.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-3">11. Termination</h2>
                <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">
                    We may suspend or terminate your access to the Service at any time, with or without cause, and with
                    or without notice. Upon termination, your right to use the Service ceases immediately.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-3">12. Contact</h2>
                <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">
                    If you have questions about these Terms, please contact us at
                    <a href="mailto:hello@airgap.health" class="text-sky-600 hover:text-sky-700 underline">hello@airgap.health</a>.
                </p>
            </section>
        </div>
    </main>

    <!-- Simple Footer for legal pages -->
    <footer class="bg-slate-900 py-8 px-4 text-center text-sm text-slate-400 mt-16">
        <p>&copy; 2026 Airgap Gate. All rights reserved.</p>
        <div class="mt-2 space-x-4">
            <a href="/terms" class="hover:text-white transition">Terms</a>
            <a href="/privacy" class="hover:text-white transition">Privacy</a>
            <a href="/" class="hover:text-white transition">Home</a>
        </div>
    </footer>
</BaseLayout>
